item.title: Basic deck box with customisable swappable badges
item.description:
A simple deck box, with room for 100 double sleeved cards, and magnetic latching.

The key feature is the quick swappable and customisable badges, allowing the deck boxes to be customised to the game or deck that you are playing. The badges are available here: https://www.prusaprinters.org/prints/122300-customisable-magnets-for-deck-boxes-mtg

It needs nine 10x3mm magnets (eight to close, one for the badge).
item.author: martin_au

item.title: Customisable magnets for deck boxes
item.description:
These are customisable magnets for use with deck boxes, or anywhere else you can imagine.

They are designed for these two deck boxes:

The basic one - https://www.prusaprinters.org/prints/122299-basic-deck-box-with-customisable-swappable-badges
or
https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:5220436

The geared deckbox with magnetic latching and a rising card platform - https://www.etsy.com/au/listing/1150943664
Want a special badge? I've included a blank badge that you can use to emboss your own patterns or text.

Want to use the badges on a different deck box? I've also included a “cutout” that can be used to cut out the area needed for the badges.

Each badge/cutout has a slight rise at the top surface to facilitate both ease of printing (no horizontal overhangs) and ease of removal of the badge. The base of each badge has a small raised section to ensure it can only be inserted one way. It uses a pair of 10x3mm magnets.
item.author: martin_au

item.title: Stand for Xiaomi HAYLOU Smart Watch Solar (LS05)
item.description:
Cool and ergonomic stand for a popular smart watch Xiaomi HAYLOU Solar (LS05).

The stand can be printed with or without supports. For this, several options for STL files are provided.

ls05-A.stl and ls05-B.stl - are not require support. You will only need to glue the two halves together (the best variant is CH2Cl2 - Dichloromethane).

ls05-full.stl - is a full model to print stand with supports.

Subscribe to my 3D Instagram - https://www.instagram.com/viktor.hodiatskyi/

item.title: Holy Hand Grenade of Antioch
item.description: This is a remix of Gsohm's Holy Hand Grenade. It has 5 changes... A hole in the crest to accommodate the cross. A hole in the top to do same. An extension of the cross to act as pin on the grenade. And two strips of PLA across the bottom and top to extend and trap the 3D raft so that supports to the middle won't come loose during the print, these strips are only 1x0.5 mm wide so as to be removed after the build. Remodelled with Openscad. Imported STL and added (or subtracted) as needed.

item.title: Mario Automaton
item.description: My partner and I were assigned the job of creating an automaton for this project. Automatons are basic systems that use cams and followers to perform a repeating motion or function. My partner and I came up with the idea of creating a "Super Mario video game scene" in which various characters from the game do simple actions to bring the setting to reality.  The hypnotic motions of the cams that lift and descend the followers are all controlled by a simple lever twist! This 23.5cm X 7.5cm X 16.5cm piece turned out great! This is also a very fun project if you are a fan of Mario!
item.author: nyacoub2024

item.title: [FD3S RX7] Cowl Screw Cover Kit
item.description:
Who isn't missing a cowl screw cover at this point? After years of sitting exposed to the elements the OEM plastic cowl screw covers weaken to the point of being extremely brittle causing them to just disintegrate by looking at them.

Sadly there is no way to buy OEM replacement screw covers, at least there wasn't until now! We're happy to offer a full direct replacement kit for the cowl screw covers. The kit includes 2 large oval screw covers and 6 small circle covers.
